                           in Virginia, however, led to the withdrawal of many federal soldiers from North Carolina, leaving only enough Union troops
                           to hold a few coastal strongholds&#8212;the vital ports and railroad junctions. The South during the Civil War, moreover,
                           hotly contested the North&#8217;s ability to maintain its grip on these key coastal strongholds.</SPAN></P>
